verbose_text: TWEAK causes sustained activation of NF-kappaB and the inhibition of NF-kappaB through overexpression of a kinase dead mutant of IKKbeta (an upstream activator of NF-kappaB) or IkappaBalphaDeltaN (a degradation resistant mutant of NF-kappaB inhibitory protein IkappaBalpha) rescued myogenic differentiation in TWEAK treated C2C12 myoblasts [XREF_BIBR].
evidence: NF-kappaB and the inhibition of NF-kappaB through overexpression of a kinase dead mutant of IKKbeta (an upstream activator of NF-kappaB) or IkappaBalphaDeltaN (a degradation resistant mutant of NF-kappaB inhibitory protein IkappaBalpha) rescued myogenic differentiation
